title: Here's who might be most affected by a clarified Section 230

title: Top Stocks To Buy Today As Markets Jump After Three Consecutive Down Days
text: After a losing streak of three straight days, stocks rose sharply based on good vaccine news and strong retail data. For investors looking to make sense of these unprecedented times, our deep learning algorithms have crunched the data to give you a set of Top Buys.

title: Wall Street Week Ahead: Big tech nervousness prompts calls to diversify
text: As a technology-driven rally brings U.S. stock indexes within striking distance of fresh records, concerns that big names are over-extended and that new regulation might be coming have some investors diversifying beyond the rally leaders.

title: AlphaOne's Dan Niles on how scrutiny of Twitter and Facebook could move investors
text: Dan Niles of AlphaOne Capital joins "Squawk Alley" to discuss regulatory scrutiny on Facebook and Twitter after the platforms chose to limit a story from the New York Post.

title: Facebook to crack down on Instagram influencers over illegal â€˜hidden advertising' after a regulator probe
text: Instagram has agreed with regulators to make a host of changes targeted at social media influencers, over concerns about hidden advertising on the platform.

title: Rep. Ro Khanna and Kevin O'Leary on Facebook, Twitter restricting New York Post story
text: Facebook and Twitter are facing criticism after limiting the reach of a New York Post story about alleged smoking gun emails showing Hunter Biden introducing his father to a Ukranian businessman. FCC chairman Ajit Pai now says he plans to "clarify" the scope of section 230, which protects platforms from being held liable for users' posts.

title: Instagram vows to fight hidden ads amid UK competition probe
text: The changes apply to all Instagram users in the U.K. and anyone globally who directs their posts toward Brits.
